{{Infobox royalty | name = Muhammad V | image = | alt = | caption = | succession = [[List of Ottoman governors of Algiers|Dey of Algiers]] | moretext = | reign = 1766&nbsp;– 1791 | coronation = | cor-type = | predecessor = [[Baba Ali II Pasha]] | regent = | reg-type = | successor = [[Baba Hassan]] | birth_date = | birth_place = Unknown | death_date = 1791 | death_place = [[Algiers]], [[Ottoman Algeria]] [[File:Fictitious Ottoman flag 2.svg|15px]] | spouse = | issue = | issue-link = | full name = Baba Mohammed ben-Osman | house = | father = | mother = | date of burial = | place of burial = | signature = }} [[File:Fictitious Ottoman flag 2.svg|thumb|Flag of Ottoman Algeria]]
'''Baba Mohammed ben-Osman''' or Muhammad V ben Othman was [[Dey]] of [[Ottoman Algeria]] from 1766 to 1791. Under his rule he declared war against [[Denmark-Norway]] because he demanded that an annual payment to stave off piracy by Denmark-Norway should be increased, and he should receive new gifts. [[Denmark-Norway]] refused the demands, beginning the [[Danish-Algerian War]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Krigen mod Algier|url=http://natmus.dk/historisk-viden/temaer/militaerhistorie/danmarks-krige/krigen-mod-algier/|website=natmus.dk|publisher=[[National Museum of Denmark]] |language=Danish}}</ref>
