'''Democratic Angola – Coalition''' ({{lang-pt|Angola Democrática – Coligação }}, also known as '''AD–Coligação''') is an alliance of [[political party|political parties]] in [[Angola]]. The leading force in AD–Coligação is the [[Front for Democracy (Angola)|Front for Democracy]] (FpD). The president of the alliance is [[Evidor Quiela]]. The alliance was formed in 1992.

In the [[Elections in Angola|1992 parliamentary election]] AD–Coligação won one seat in the national assembly, with 0.86% of the national vote. The seat is held by [[João Vieira Lopes]], from the FpD. The presidential candidate of AD–Coligação was [[Simão Cassete]], who got 0,67% of the votes. Cassete left Angola after the elections, and is now the representative of FpD in [[Europe]].

