{{EngvarB|date=March 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox radio station | name = Mutiara FM | image = Mutiara FM Logo.png | city = [[Kuala Lumpur]] | area = [[West Malaysia]] | branding = | slogan = | frequency = Varies depending on its region | translator = | repeater = | airdate = <!-- {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes}} --> | last airdate = <!-- for defunct stations --> | share = | share as of = | share source = | format = [[Talk radio|Talk]], [[contemporary hit radio]] | language = [[Malay language|Malay]] | power = | erp = | haat = | class = | facility_id = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|}} --> | callsign_meaning = | former_callsigns = | former_frequencies = <!-- use – --> | affiliations = | owner = [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]] | licensee = | sister_stations = [[Asyik FM]], Bintulu FM, [[Johor FM]], IKIM.fm, Kedah FM, Kelantan FM, Keningau FM, [[KL FM]], Labuan FM, Langkawi FM, Limbang FM, [[Malacca FM]], Miri FM, Mutiara FM, [[Negeri FM]], [[Pahang FM]], Perak FM, Perlis FM, RaSa FM, Red FM, Sabah FM, Sabah Vfm, Sandakan FM, [[Sarawak FM]], [[Selangor FM]], Sibu FM, Tawau FM, Terengganu FM, UFM and Wai FM | webcast = | website = {{URL|http://mutiarafm.rtm.gov.my/}} }}
'''Mutiara FM''' is a [[Malay language]]-regional [[radio station]] operated by [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]], [[broadcasting]] out of the Penang state capital [[George Town, Penang|George Town]] in [[Malaysia]]. It broadcasts every day in [[Malay language|Malay]] from 06:00 until 00:00 featuring local [[news]] and national [[music]]. It transmits from Bukit Penara on [[frequency modulation|FM]] 95.7&nbsp;MHz (main), and through two other low-power transmitters (FM 93.9&nbsp;MHz for North [[Penang]] and FM 90.9&nbsp;MHz in the Western part of Penang Island).
== Etymology == The station was formerly known as Radio Malaysia Pulau Pinang and Radio 3 Pulau Pinang. The current name is used since April 2005.
== Frequencies == * 95.7 MHz from Bukit Penara covers Georgetown, Seberang Perai (Central-South Penang), South Kedah (Kulim and Selama) and North Perak (Parit Buntar, Bagan Serai, Semanggol, Batu Kurau and parts of Taiping) * 90.9 MHz from Bukit Genting covers Balik Pulau * 93.9 MHz from Gunung Jerai covers Batu Feringgi, Tanjung Bungah, North Penang (Kepala Batas) and parts of Central Kedah (Yan, Sungai Petani, Gurun and parts of Alor Setar)
== External links == * {{official|http://mutiarafm.rtm.gov.my/}}
