{{Coord|0|35|0|N|131|11|33|E|display=title}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name = Pulau Reni | motto = | website = | image_seal = | image_skyline= | pushpin_map = Indonesia West Papua | map_caption = Location of Pulau Reni in [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]] | pushpin_map1 = Indonesia | pushpin_map_caption1 = Location of Pulau Reni in [[Indonesia]] | subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]] | subdivision_type1 = [[Government Administration in Indonesia#Province|Province]] | subdivision_name = {{flag|Indonesia}} | subdivision_name1 = {{flag|West Papua}} | leader_title = | leader_name = | established_title = | established_date = | area_magnitude = | area_total_km2 = | area_land_km2 = 0.92 | area_water_km2 = | population_as_of = | population_total = | timezone = Eastern Indonesian Time | utc_offset = +09:00 | coordinates = {{coord|0|35|0|N|131|11|33|E|region:ID|display=inline}} | footnotes = }} {{Infobox islands |name = Pulau Reni |image_name = Karta ID RajaAmpat Isl.PNG |locator_map = |native_name = |native_name_link = |location = [[South East Asia]] |coordinates= {{coord|0|22|N|131|02|E|region:ID_type:isle}} |archipelago = [[Ayu Islands]] |total_islands = 5 (2 uninhabited) |major_islands = [[Pulau Ayu]], Pulau Reni, [[Pulau Kanobe]] |area_km2 = |highest_mount = |elevation_m = |country = {{flag|Indonesia}} |country_admin_divisions_title = Province |country_admin_divisions = {{flag|West Papua}} |country_largest_city = |country_largest_city_population = |population = |population_as_of = |density_km2 = |ethnic_groups =[[Melanesians]], [[Papuan peoples|Papuans]], [[Austronesian peoples|Austronesians]] |image_caption = Location of Pulau Reni listed as Ayau ([[Ayu Islands]]) in the [[Raja Ampat Islands]] located in the top right corner of the map}}
'''Pulau Reni''' is a small [[Indonesia]]n island located in the [[Ayu Islands|Ayu Archipelago]] above the northern tip of the [[Waigeo]] Islands.
Pulau Reni is part of the [[Raja Ampat]] regency of the [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]] geographical and administrative region of [[Indonesia]].
The island is surrounded by two large [[reefs]].
[[Pulau Ayu]] and [[Pulau Kanobe]] are two other small inhabited islands south-west and south of Pulau Reni.
Pulau Reni lies {{convert|27|km|abbr=on}} north-east of [[Pulau Ayu]] and {{convert|11|km|abbr=on}} north of Pulau Kanobe.
Access to the island is limited to small [[boats]] due to the reefs and the small size of the island.
==World War II== Pulau Reni and all the islands in the Ayu Archipelago were occupied by the [[Japanese Empire]] during [[World War II]] from 1942 until the end of the war in 1945.
