{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = San Pedro-en-Côte d'Ivoire |latin = Dioecesis Sancti Petri in Litore Eburneo |country = Côte d'Ivoire |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gagnoa|Gagnoa]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |area_km2 = 30,375 |population = 1,100,000 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 60,000 |catholics_percent= 5.5 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Paulin Kouabenan N’Gname]] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of San Pedro-en-Côte d'Ivoire''' ({{lang-la|Sancti Petri in Litore Eburneo}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[San Pedro, Côte d'Ivoire|San Pedro]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gagnoa|Gagnoa]] in [[Côte d'Ivoire]].
==History== * October 23, 1989: Established as Diocese of San Pedro-en-Côte-d’Ivoire from Diocese of Gagnoa
==Special churches== The [[Cathedral]] is the Cathédrale St. Pierre in San Pedro.
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of San Pedro-en-Côte d'Ivoire (Roman rite) ** Bishop [[Jean-Jacques Koffi Oi Koffi]] (since 2009.01.03) ** Bishop [[Paulin Kouabénan N'Gnamé]] (2007.03.01 – 2008.03.21) ** Archbishop [[Barthélémy Djabla]] (1989.10.23 – 2006.07.21)
